Errors vs No-Errors
----------------------
If comments and set-delim tags are going to be skipped, I think the scanner will need to return errors. 
For example:
    "abcd{{! my comment }efgh"

The example above has a malformed closing delim, causing the lexer to consider all remaining text after the openning
bracket to be commented text - i.e. "my comment }efgh" - and the EOF would occur before the closing tag was ever found.
This should lead to some error such as "closing tag not found". Without error messages, there might not be any good
way to report this error.

However, 
